cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the computation of shortest paths in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new data structure, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of logarithmic time and space complexities suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GR (Graph Theory). Finally, the extension of the problem to a weighted rectilinear version suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
